00:12:36,070 --> 00:12:38,270
You don't have confidence in yourself?

285
00:12:44,550 --> 00:12:45,310
Do you know

286
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:46,430
Google?

287
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:48,430
Yes, I do.

288
00:12:48,830 --> 00:12:50,830
The best search engine in the world.

289
00:12:50,830 --> 00:12:52,460
When Google started,

290
00:12:52,460 --> 00:12:54,310
Yahoo was already there,

291
00:12:54,310 --> 00:12:56,450
which was the world's number one search engine,

292
00:12:56,450 --> 00:12:57,970
an internet giant.

293
00:12:58,790 --> 00:13:01,070
Even Silicon Valley investors tried to dissuade Google,

294
00:13:01,070 --> 00:13:02,630
saying that with Yahoo ahead,

295
00:13:02,630 --> 00:13:04,030
they'd have no future.

296
00:13:05,370 --> 00:13:06,930
But they didn't give up.

297
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:09,110
They persevered in the search engine field

298
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:11,030
and carved out their own space.

299
00:13:11,430 --> 00:13:12,230
Let me ask you,

300
00:13:12,770 --> 00:13:13,970
what was the key

301
00:13:14,590 --> 00:13:15,590
to their success?

302
00:13:16,110 --> 00:13:17,320
Technology, I guess.

303
00:13:17,350 --> 00:13:19,410
And what's the source of technology?

304
00:13:22,150 --> 00:13:22,940
Knowledge.

305
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:24,250
And

306
00:13:25,140 --> 00:13:26,660
deep thinking.

307
00:13:28,460 --> 00:13:29,790
In terms of mere knowledge,

308
00:13:29,790 --> 00:13:31,600
I believe with your IQ,

309
00:13:31,630 --> 00:13:33,030
even if you study at home,

310
00:13:33,590 --> 00:13:35,020
you can still manage.

311
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,800
But systematic learning

312
00:13:36,830 --> 00:13:38,830
can help you establish

313
00:13:39,340 --> 00:13:42,910
a scientific and effective thinking framework in the shortest time.

314
00:13:42,910 --> 00:13:44,450
It's like the foundation.

315
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:47,050
How tall a building can be

316
00:13:47,340 --> 00:13:50,330
depends on how deep its foundation is,

317
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:51,060
right?

318
00:13:52,150 --> 00:13:52,980
Last time,

319
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:55,730
you mentioned that ebony wood

320
00:13:55,980 --> 00:13:57,180
is priceless.

321
00:13:57,380 --> 00:13:58,510
It was a great point.

322
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:00,400
But have you thought about this?

323
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:03,770
For a tree to become ebony wood,

324
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,220
it's not just about the passage of time.

325
00:14:07,230 --> 00:14:09,820
First, it has to be a tree,

326
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:11,490
and it has to grow well.

327
00:14:13,810 --> 00:14:15,470
If it were green foxtail,

328
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:18,050
even after thousands of years,

329
00:14:18,350 --> 00:14:20,410
it still wouldn't become ebony wood.

330
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:20,970
Right?

331
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:27,910
Mr. Xu, this...

332
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:28,830
This is great.

333
00:14:28,850 --> 00:14:30,690
Did you hear that?

334
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:32,080
Mr. Xu was praising you,

335
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:33,760
saying you're promising.

336
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:36,850
Mr. Xu.

337
00:14:36,990 --> 00:14:37,970
Did you hear that?

338
00:14:37,970 --> 00:14:39,450
You must study hard.

339
00:14:39,490 --> 00:14:40,820
If you don't study well,

340
00:14:40,930 --> 00:14:43,130
your dad and I will beat you up together.

341
00:14:44,910 --> 00:14:46,100
Mr... Mr. Xu.

342
00:14:46,130 --> 00:14:49,370
Please take extra care of him at school.

343
00:14:55,950 --> 00:14:56,480
Alright.

344
00:14:57,430 --> 00:14:59,550
I'll also count on you, Wanghe's mom.

345
00:14:59,810 --> 00:15:01,650
After all, with the support of parents,

346
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:03,000
we teachers

347
00:15:03,350 --> 00:15:05,630
can do more with less,

348
00:15:05,660 --> 00:15:06,350
right?

349
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:07,130
Sure. Sure.

350
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,920
P-Please take extra care of him.

351
00:15:10,150 --> 00:15:11,110
Well,

352
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:13,390
since we're not at school after all,

353
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:15,520
we don't know what's going on in there.

354
00:15:15,740 --> 00:15:18,270
If he misbehaves at school,

355
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:19,790
just discipline him as needed.

356
00:15:19,790 --> 00:15:20,950
His father and I

357
00:15:20,980 --> 00:15:21,820
don't mind.

358
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:23,370
But Mr. Xu does.

359
00:15:24,850 --> 00:15:26,490
Alright, I'll be on my way.

360
00:15:26,850 --> 00:15:27,380
Alright.

361
00:15:27,670 --> 00:15:29,130
Thank you for everything.

362
00:15:29,290 --> 00:15:30,390
Goodbye, Mr. Xu.

363
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:31,520
Alright, goodbye.

364
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:37,600
I won't hit you,

365
00:15:38,830 --> 00:15:39,900
but with your father's temper,

366
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:41,760
you better think about what to do.

367
00:15:56,990 --> 00:15:57,770
Mr. Xu has left?

368
00:15:57,770 --> 00:15:58,450
Yes.

369
00:15:58,550 --> 00:15:59,520
How was it?

370
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:00,820
Are you two alright?

371
00:16:00,850 --> 00:16:02,740
You owe us both a beating.

372
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:04,670
How was Beijing?

373
00:16:05,430 --> 00:16:06,270
It was alright.

374
00:16:06,270 --> 00:16:07,800
Did you go to Zhongguancun?

375
00:16:08,070 --> 00:16:08,790
I did.

376
00:16:08,820 --> 00:16:10,290
It's not quite what I imagined.

377
00:16:10,290 --> 00:16:11,620
Don't leave already.

378
00:16:11,650 --> 00:16:12,580
Tell us about it.

379
00:16:12,990 --> 00:16:15,390
How's it different from your imagination?

380
00:16:19,260 --> 00:16:21,010
Before going to Beijing,

381
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:23,860
I thought I was smarter than everyone else.

382
00:16:23,860 --> 00:16:25,470
I thought I could see further into the future than anyone.

383
00:16:25,470 --> 00:16:26,890
But after I got there, I realized

384
00:16:26,890 --> 00:16:28,540
there are too many smart people.

385
00:16:28,540 --> 00:16:30,560
Taking a stroll around Zhongguancun,

386
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:31,470
I saw graduates

387
00:16:31,590 --> 00:16:33,450
from top universities across the country

388
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:34,880
all struggling

389
00:16:34,900 --> 00:16:35,900
and working hard.

390
00:16:36,810 --> 00:16:38,510
Everyone already knows

391
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:39,780
those little tricks I learned online,

392
00:16:39,780 --> 00:16:42,510
and they're already putting them into practice.

393
00:16:42,570 --> 00:16:44,570
Only after going there did I realize

394
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:46,810
I was just like a frog in a well.

395
00:16:47,150 --> 00:16:48,750
So what are you thinking now?

396
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,100
I haven't figured it out yet.

397
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:53,970
I think

398
00:16:54,230 --> 00:16:55,660
maybe you should give it a shot

399
00:16:55,660 --> 00:16:57,390
and try to get into university.

400
00:16:57,530 --> 00:16:58,830
Even if it's not for your parents,

401
00:16:58,830 --> 00:17:00,620
you'll have more options in the future.

402
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:01,420
That's right.

403
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:03,800
With your brains,

404
00:17:03,810 --> 00:17:04,960
if you really work hard for the exam,

405
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:07,790
you could at least get into a second-tier university.

406
00:17:07,790 --> 00:17:09,920
Is it a matter of taking the exam or not?

407
00:17:10,099 --> 00:17:11,760
Given my family's situation,

408
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:13,130
and Siyi...

409
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:16,150
Siyi is going to try to get enrolled in a normal university, which is tuition-free.

410
00:17:16,150 --> 00:17:17,329
Your dad should be able to make some money

411
00:17:17,329 --> 00:17:18,740
from selling the ship.

412
00:17:23,829 --> 00:17:25,560
When our parents tell us

413
00:17:25,589 --> 00:17:26,859
they're doing things for our own good,

414
00:17:26,859 --> 00:17:28,150
isn't it really annoying?

415
00:17:28,150 --> 00:17:29,430
It's the same the other way around.

416
00:17:29,430 --> 00:17:30,500
When you do things for your parents' good,

417
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:31,750
don't they get annoyed too?

418
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:32,700
They do.

419
00:17:33,660 --> 00:17:35,320
Don't take this the wrong way,

420
00:17:35,510 --> 00:17:36,710
but what you're doing

421
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:38,600
is called emotional blackmail.

422
00:18:26,460 --> 00:18:28,470
Why are you wearing so much in this weather?

423
00:18:28,470 --> 00:18:30,600
Are you going to the North Pole or what?

424
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:34,970
Wanghe is definitely going to get a beating tonight.

425
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:37,140
Your Uncle Xie said

426
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:39,050
he wanted to teach him a lesson.

427
00:18:39,340 --> 00:18:40,670
I have to try to stop it a bit,

428
00:18:40,670 --> 00:18:43,200
right? We can't let the kid get hurt too badly.

429
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,280
He won't.

430
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:47,790
Do you think Wanghe is the type to take a beating quietly?

431
00:18:47,790 --> 00:18:49,160
If it really hurts,

432
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:50,310
he'll beg for mercy.

433
00:18:50,430 --> 00:18:51,480
There are things you don't know.

434
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:53,040
Your Uncle Xie has been

435
00:18:53,320 --> 00:18:54,810
in a bad mood lately.

436
00:18:55,130 --> 00:18:58,030
I'm worried he might not stop once he starts beating him,

437
00:18:58,030 --> 00:18:58,860
unable to control himself.

438
00:18:58,860 --> 00:18:59,860
He's in a bad mood?

439
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:04,800
Are you really going to sell the ship?

440
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:06,550
How do you know?

441
00:19:07,510 --> 00:19:08,610
My mom told me.

442
00:19:09,030 --> 00:19:10,230
Has Uncle Xie agreed?

443
00:19:15,100 --> 00:19:17,030
Business hasn't been good lately.

444
00:19:18,930 --> 00:19:20,660
After selling the ship, we'll see if we can

445
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:21,960
find something else to do.

446
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:23,390
Besides seafaring,

447
00:19:23,490 --> 00:19:24,620
what else can you do?

448
00:19:25,490 --> 00:19:26,460
Why would you say that?

449
00:19:26,460 --> 00:19:28,590
You're looking down on me, aren't you?

450
00:19:28,770 --> 00:19:29,890
Let me tell you,

451
00:19:30,310 --> 00:19:33,360
Fenghua, back in the day, your Uncle Xie and I

452
00:19:33,390 --> 00:19:35,070
traveled all over the country.

453
00:19:35,070 --> 00:19:36,230
We've done so many businesses,

454
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:37,990
like electronic watches and foreign cigarettes.

455
00:19:37,990 --> 00:19:39,450
You don't know how many of those we bought and resold.

456
00:19:39,450 --> 00:19:40,470
We even ran a video hall once,

457
00:19:40,470 --> 00:19:42,670
showing Hong Kong and Taiwan films, action movies, and romance movies.

458
00:19:42,670 --> 00:19:44,190
Your mom loved watching those the most.

459
00:19:44,190 --> 00:19:45,970
What nonsense are you talking about?

460
00:19:45,970 --> 00:19:48,630
It was "The Legend of the Condor Heroes", right?

461
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:51,130
We did whatever was profitable back then.

462
00:19:52,660 --> 00:19:54,060
So why can't you do it now?

463
00:19:56,620 --> 00:19:57,270
Well...

464
00:19:58,090 --> 00:19:59,980
It's not that we can't do it now.

465
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:03,660
But after all, times have changed.

466
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:04,780
right?

467
00:20:05,230 --> 00:20:07,430
We need to find a new way to make a living.

468
00:20:09,010 --> 00:20:11,670
In recent years, so many people lost their jobs,

469
00:20:11,820 --> 00:20:14,150
but I haven't seen anyone starve to death.

470
00:20:21,790 --> 00:20:22,710
Dad.

471
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:24,540
I actually have an idea.

472
00:20:24,570 --> 00:20:26,300
You don't have to sell the ship.

473
00:20:26,470 --> 00:20:27,250
Really?

474
00:20:29,310 --> 00:20:31,160
If this idea can be implemented,

475
00:20:31,190 --> 00:20:32,950
Uncle Xie won't feel so bad anymore,

476
00:20:32,950 --> 00:20:35,550
and Wanghe might be able to avoid this beating.

477
00:20:41,750 --> 00:20:46,170
♫Girl, you sit on the bow♫

478
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:49,530
♫I tow the boat on the shore♫

479
00:20:50,870 --> 00:20:55,160
♫In deep love♫

480
00:20:56,280 --> 00:20:56,810
Bro.

481
00:20:58,140 --> 00:20:59,540
You went drinking again.

482
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:00,340
Lao'er.

483
00:21:00,390 --> 00:21:01,260
You're still up?

484
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,430
Yeah.

485
00:21:02,460 --> 00:21:05,430
There's something I want to discuss with you.

486
00:21:07,730 --> 00:21:08,390
Be careful.

487
00:21:08,420 --> 00:21:09,100
Alright.

488
00:21:09,470 --> 00:21:10,090
Go ahead.

489
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,310
Here's the thing.

490
00:21:13,410 --> 00:21:14,650
It's my daughter's idea.

491
00:21:14,650 --> 00:21:16,250
A floating supermarket.

492
00:21:17,420 --> 00:21:19,110
That is to say, we stock up on goods

493
00:21:19,110 --> 00:21:20,510
and sell them on the ship.

494
00:21:20,590 --> 00:21:21,770
We can make extra money

495
00:21:21,770 --> 00:21:22,790
while seafaring.

496
00:21:22,810 --> 00:21:24,280
It'll be killing two birds with one stone, right?

497
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,590
Let me finish, bro.

498
00:21:27,140 --> 00:21:29,170
Tell me, how many seafaring ships

499
00:21:29,530 --> 00:21:31,150
are there on the river now?

500
00:21:31,550 --> 00:21:32,900
Talking about setting up a floating supermarket.

501
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:34,710
Who are you going to sell the goods to?

502
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:37,410
You'd be better off setting up a roasted sweet potato stand by the roadside.

503
00:21:37,410 --> 00:21:39,160
It would be more profitable than this.

504
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:40,950
It's not like that, bro.

505
00:21:41,710 --> 00:21:42,480
About this matter,

506
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:45,670
Yan also thinks we could give it a try.

507
00:21:46,260 --> 00:21:47,390
You're listening to

508
00:21:47,410 --> 00:21:48,670
women's opinions now?

509
00:21:52,430 --> 00:21:53,470
Don't worry.

510
00:21:53,990 --> 00:21:56,760
Even if we can't do seafaring business anymore,

511
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:58,330
as long as you stick with me,

512
00:21:58,710 --> 00:21:59,820
you won't be poor.

513
00:22:09,510 --> 00:22:10,280
How did it go?

514
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:14,150
He didn't agree?

515
00:22:14,870 --> 00:22:16,790
I'll talk to him again later.

516
00:22:16,910 --> 00:22:18,490
How about we ask Wanghe to talk to him?

517
00:22:18,490 --> 00:22:19,500
He's quick-witted.

518
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:20,280
When it comes to making money,

519
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:21,480
I think Uncle Xie will listen to him.

520
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:22,860
Why bother talking to him?

521
00:22:22,860 --> 00:22:25,590
He used to make the call on everything on the ship,

522
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:27,820
and now we still have to listen to him about opening the supermarket or not?

523
00:22:27,820 --> 00:22:29,280
It's none of his business!

524
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:31,240
We're so poor that we can barely put food on the table.

525
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:32,240
If we still don't have any income in the near future,

526
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:34,780
the whole family will be left with nothing to eat.

527
00:22:34,780 --> 00:22:35,800
What's wrong with you?

528
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:36,630
Why are you saying these things

529
00:22:36,630 --> 00:22:37,710
in front of our daughter?

530
00:22:37,710 --> 00:22:39,750
You're just too easily swayed.

531
00:22:39,940 --> 00:22:41,780
You're a grown man, yet you don't have your own opinions.

532
00:22:41,780 --> 00:22:43,210
You always listen to Boss Xie on everything.

533
00:22:43,210 --> 00:22:44,380
Who's listening to him?

534
00:22:44,380 --> 00:22:46,240
You just won't let it go, will you?

535
00:22:59,190 --> 00:23:00,990
This is ridiculous.

536
00:23:02,160 --> 00:23:03,390
Don't go in yet.

537
00:23:03,390 --> 00:23:04,270
I have something to ask you.

538
00:23:04,270 --> 00:23:06,730
Wait until I'm done beating him up.

539
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:09,220
You're not listening to me anymore, are you?

540
00:23:09,370 --> 00:23:11,340
Wanghe mentioned his idea of dropping out of school

541
00:23:11,340 --> 00:23:12,880
to you before, right?

542
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:14,440
He mentioned it briefly.

543
00:23:14,570 --> 00:23:16,300
Why didn't you tell me about it?

544
00:23:16,560 --> 00:23:17,030
Well,

545
00:23:17,030 --> 00:23:19,190
I didn't expect him to just

546
00:23:19,190 --> 00:23:20,250
go through with it.

547
00:23:20,630 --> 00:23:21,610
Wanghe said

548
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:23,810
